#### Step 6: Cache on Successful API Load

In `useInventory` or the POS page, cache data whenever it loads:

```ts
const { data: serverProducts } = useInventory(storeId);

useEffect(() => {
  if (serverProducts?.length) {
    cacheProducts(serverProducts);  // Save to IndexedDB
  }
}, [serverProducts]);
```

### Key UX Rules

- Show a persistent offline banner with pending transaction count
- Only allow CASH payments offline — card/NFC buttons disabled with tooltip
- Auto-sync when connection is restored (via `navigator.onLine` event)
- Show sync progress indicator (e.g. “Syncing 3/5…”)
- If sync fails 3 times, mark as FAILED and alert the manager
- Barcode scanning works offline (local product lookup via IndexedDB)
- Receipt printing works offline (local printer, no server needed)
- ID scanning for age verification does NOT work offline (use manual DOB or visual)

### Offline Limitations (Display to User)

- ❌ Card/NFC payments
- ❌ AI upsell suggestions
- ❌ SMS sending
- ❌ Loyalty point redemption
- ❌ Real-time stock from other registers
- ✅ Cash sales
- ✅ Barcode scanning
- ✅ Product search (cached)
- ✅ Customer lookup (cached)
- ✅ Receipt printing (local)
- ✅ Age verification (manual/visual)

